etymologies: late Middle English: from Anglo-Norman French deforcer, from de- (expressing removal) + forcer ‘to force’

definitions: withhold (land or other property) wrongfully or forcibly from the rightful owner.
shortDefinitions: withhold land or other property wrongfully or forcibly from rightful owner

definitions: deprive (someone) wrongfully or forcibly of rightful property.
shortDefinitions: deprive someone wrongfully or forcibly of rightful property
